stocks with large marketcaps and high daily trading volumes adrs preferred stocks and foreign stocks may also be based on client guidelines sarofim invests in the stocks of high quality financially sound industry leaders that have an expanding global presence they maintain a longerterm investment approach of at least  years which generally results in low portfolio turnover and is typically tax efficient for taxable investors the strategy does not use derivatives options shortselling leverage or ipos sarofim does not attempt to time the marketsarofims global equity product is suitable for institutions and individuals seeking greater international equity exposure while the investment approach is similar to that of their largecap equity product the global equity product has a larger concentration in foreignbased companies and may include shares that are not traded on domestic exchangessarofim also offers a core fixed income product which is available to both institutions and individuals the strategy emphasizes riskaverse management current income and low cash reserves portfolio holdings may include us treasury securities us government agency securities high quality corporate bonds high quality commercial paper and shares of money market funds sarofim selects specific sectors and securities that they believe offer the best combination of quality liquidity income generation and relative value consistent with their risk parameters foreign government and foreign corporate bonds are generally not part of this strategysarofim also constructs balanced portfolios for institutional and individual clients these portfolios combine the firm’s equity and fixed income strategies in proportions tailored to client requirements director vice president  assistant secretary    sarofim trust co vice president assistant secretary    sarofim advisors group inc sarofim advisors group inc a subsidiary of the sarofim group inc is an american company located in houston tx that provides investment advice senior principal   prior fayez sarofim  co fayez sarofim  co manages investment portfolios for a wide range of clients — pension plans foundations endowments and individuals for over five decades since our founding in  we have focused exclusively on investment management our firm is an independent entity owned and managed by its founder fayez sarofim and a team of  investment professionals as of june   our firm had  billion in assets under management boards  committees nonprofit boards ▾ member board of directors current alley theatre professional resident theatre whose mission is to produce great theatre that embodies the resident company member board of directors tenure unconfirmed trees for houston trees for houston grows plants and maintains trees throughout the greater houston area mission related activities include outdoor and inclass educational programming volunteer projects and urban forestry information as well as the management of six tree farms political donations   david h dewhurst   john mccain senator from arizona   rudolph w giuliani chair cybersecurity privacy  crisis management practice senior advisor to the executive chairman at greenberg traurig llp   straight talk america other affiliations robert melburn hopson iii is affiliated with sarofim realty advisors co sarofim international management co sarofim trust co sarofim advisors group inc fayez sarofim  co alley theatre trees for houston youve reached your  free profiles limit this month upgrade to relsci pro today to enjoy unlimited article views and much more start my free trial ➤ still not convinced check out our full listing of features here are you a relsci pro subscriber login to relsci pro  ➤ not a pro subscriber log in here to manage your alerts keep me signed in login  ➤ forgot your password i have read the lexisnexis terms  conditions sign me up  ➤ microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow firstparty 